## Git Workflow Rules

### Branch Management
- Always create a new branch for each feature (check for existing relevant branches first)
- Use naming convention: `feat-feature-name` for features
- Create PRs when finishing a feature and ensure no merge conflicts before merging
- Make frequent commits - commit after every small change or logical unit of work
- Never commit directly to main - always use feature branches

### File Structure
React file structure should be:
- `core/` - Types, contexts, .ts files, utilities (anything that doesn't belong in views/components)
- `components/` - Reusable components sorted into:
  - `ComponentName/`
    - `index.ts` - Export file
    - `ComponentName.tsx` - Component file
    - `ComponentName.css` - Styles
- `views/` - Page-level views (same structure as components)

### Code Standards
- Use camelCase for variable names
- Keep code clean and self-commenting (no comments needed)
- Follow consistent style across all code
- Analyze the whole project before making big decisions
- Write and pass tests using Jest when necessary

### Project Context
This is a gamified 'lock in' React website and React Native app called Fixated:
- Focus: Habit tracking, progress tracking, gamification
- Features: Daily goals, ranks, leveling up, stats (strength, intelligence, etc.)
- Philosophy: Progression vs yourself (self-improvement focus)
- Visualizations: Lots of graphs/charts comparing today vs yesterday
- Skills: Library of skills (meditation, running, lifting, intelligence, reading, math, history, geography, etc.)
- Rating System: NBA 2K style out of 100 rating overall
- Major skill sections with overall ratings, minor categories with individual ratings
- Firebase: Accounts and data storage
- Separate directories for web and React Native app
- Push commits separately for web and mobile

