### Worktree Management (CRITICAL)
- **MANDATORY**: Use worktrees for parallel development
- Create worktrees for each feature branch
- Each agent works in their assigned worktree
- Commit frequently in your worktree (after every change)
- Head agent monitors and coordinates worktrees
- Clean up untracked files regularly
- Sync worktrees before starting new work
- Never work directly in main repository - always use worktrees

### Commit Guidelines
- Commit after every small change
- Use descriptive commit messages
- Format: "feat: description" or "fix: description" or "refactor: description"
- Include what was changed in commit message
- Never leave uncommitted changes overnight

### Merge Conflict Prevention
- Check for conflicts before starting work on shared files
- Coordinate with head agent if modifying core files
- Pull latest changes before starting new features
- Resolve conflicts immediately when detected

### Head Agent Responsibilities
- Monitor all worktrees continuously
- Auto-commit changes periodically
- Clean up untracked files
- Detect and report conflicts
- Assign new work to available worktrees
- Generate status reports
- Coordinate merges

### Quality Standards
- All code must be tested
- No console.logs in production code
- Handle errors gracefully
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Ensure responsive design
- Optimize for performance
